ProcedureHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: PROC DELETE <LIBRARY=libref> DATA=SAS-file-1 <SAS-file-2 …> 
    (<GENNUM=ALL | HIST | REVERT | integer> 
    <MEMTYPE=member-type> 
    <ENCRYPTKEY=key-value> 
    <ALTER=alter-password>);
    
The DELETE procedure deletes SAS files from the disk or tape on which it is stored. Use PROC DELETE 
to do the following: 

  •delete either permanent or temporary SAS files
  •delete a list of data sets with a numeric suffix, such as
    proc delete data=x1-x3;
    run;
  •delete all SAS files of the same type using MEMTYPE=
  •delete generation data sets using GENNUM=
  •delete AES encrypted data sets when using GENNUM=ALL and ENCRYPTKEY= options 
  
One of the benefits of using PROC DELETE instead of the DELETE statement in the DATASETS procedure 
is that it does not use the in-memory directory to delete SAS data sets. 

The DELETE procedure produces no printed output. As a result, the DELETE procedure is faster.

ProcedureOptionHelp.#cdata:
[Syntax: DATA= SAS-file-1 <SAS-file-2 ...>] 
      
Specifies one or more SAS files that you want to delete. 

Note:You can also use a numbered range list.

Syntax: ALTER=alter-password 
      
Provides the Alter password for any alter-protected SAS files.

Syntax: ENCRYPTKEY=key-value]
      
The ENCRYPTKEY= option unlocks the data sets that are protected by an AES-encrypted key value. 
The ENCRYPTKEY= option is needed only when a data set must be opened. Therefore, this option will 
be needed only when GENNUM=ALL is used.
Restricts processing for generation data sets.

ProcedureOptionToolTips.@ToolTip1: Refers to the base version and all historical versions in a generation group.
ProcedureOptionToolTips.@ToolTip2: Refers to all historical versions, but excludes the base version in a generation group.
ProcedureOptionToolTips.@ToolTip3: Deletes the base version and changes the most current historical version, if it exists, to the base version.
ProcedureOptionToolTips.@ToolTip4: Is a number that references a specific version from a generation group. Specifying a positive number  is an absolute reference to a specific generation number that is appended

ProcedureOptionHelp.#cdata:
[Syntax: LIBRARY=libref] 
      
Specifies a SAS name that is associated with the location of a SAS library.

[Syntax: MEMTYPE=(mtype(s))] 
      
Restricts deleting one or more member types.

ProcedureOptionToolTips.@ToolTip1: Access descriptor files (created by SAS/ACCESS software)
